ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
1 = Baseline; 2 = Post MCI; 3 = Week 4; 4 = Week 8; 5 = Week 12

ElementDescription: Receiving mental health services is something people look down upon.
Notes: 0 = Strongly disagree; 1 = Disagree; 2 = Agree; 3 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: It is a sign of personal weakness to receive psychological help.
Notes: 0 = Strongly disagree; 1 = Disagree; 2 = Agree; 3 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: People will see a person in a less favorable way if they find out that he/she has seen a therapist.
Notes: 0 = Strongly disagree; 1 = Disagree; 2 = Agree; 3 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: It is better for a person to hide from people that he/she has been treated for emotional or psychological problems.
Notes: 0 = Strongly disagree; 1 = Disagree; 2 = Agree; 3 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: People tend to like less those who are receiving professional help for an emotional/psychological problem.
Notes: 0 = Strongly disagree; 1 = Disagree; 2 = Agree; 3 = Strongly agree
